Hello,
The drive gearing is just the first number of the swerve module ratio. So yours would be 4.71.
The wheel COF is the wheel Coefficient of friction, you can likely find the exact value from whatever page you bought the swerve module wheels from. You could also measure it out yourself by measuring the force required to cause the robot to skid on the carpet (COF = Force to pull robot divided by normal force (Mass of robot * Acceleration due to gravity(9.8))). Or you could just tune the value until the robot stops slipping on the carpet.
If you have any more questions about specific elements of the Robot Config page, you can view the documentation for it at Robot Config | PathPlanner Docs.
